m_level":"System","justification":"Ordering depends on real filesystem timestamp metadata and near-simultaneous arrival timing under the live watcher. Integration can validate sorter logic, but can miss real failures from timestamp resolution/ordering and watcher delivery races. Considered Integration, rejected because behavior text ties correctness to actual file arrival timing and creation timestamps.","test_description":"Create multiple files nearly simultaneously in a real watched directory with controlled creation sequence, then assert daemon processing order matches filesystem-reported creation timestamps (including deterministic tie-breaker if timestamps are equal).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.28,"System":0.6,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"A file that is still being written to when the arrival event fires is not picked up for processing until writing is complete.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This is a real filesystem-write/readiness race (event emitted before write completion). Mocked I/O commonly hides partial-write timing and file-lock/flush behavior. Considered Integration, rejected because behavior text explicitly depends on in-progress real writes at event time.","test_description":"Start daemon, begin a slow/chunked write to a new file in the watched directory so arrival event fires before completion, verify no processing occurs mid-write, then complete/close the file and verify processing starts only after completion.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.87,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
